Interlachen Country Club is a private, invitation only club.
Nominees are endorsed by current members and subject to election to membership in accordance with the bylaws and regulations of the Club. A strong emphasis is placed upon the nominee's social and community relationships. The Club and its Membership Committee and Board will evaluate a nominee without regard to race, color, national origin, sex, religious or sexual preference, or any disabilities of the nominee.
Membership & Information
Golf member privileges include use of the golf, tennis, aquatics and fitness facilities, croquet lawn, all dining venues and attendance to all social events. Tennis/Social privileges include use of the tennis, aquatics and fitness facilities, croquet lawn, all dining venues and attendance to all social events.
Membership Fees and Dues vary by category. Please contact the Membership Office for further details.

ADMINISTRATION
Barry
Herman, CCM
General Manager
A native Floridian, Barry was born in Miami and raised in the Florida Keys, before moving to Tallahassee. He began his hospitality career in 1994 at the Governors Club, a private city club in downtown Tallahassee. Working his way through the ranks, Barry was promoted to General Manager and held that position until 2007. Before joining Interlachen in August 2012, he held the position of Assistant General Manager with Riviera Country Club in Coral Gables, Florida. Barry is a Certified Club Manager (CCM) and continues to be active in the Club Managers Association of America. When he is not working, Barry enjoys spending time with his wife and their three daughters and is an avid golfer.
Brendan Clark
Assistant General Manager
Brendan is a graduate
            of Virginia Tech where he earned a Bachelor of Science in Hospitality and
            Tourism Management. He began his Club Management career at Farmington Country
            Club in Charlottesville, Virginia after graduating from school and most
            recently served as the Clubhouse Manager at Yeamans Hall Club in Charleston,
            South Carolina. Brendan is actively involved in the Club Managers Association
            of America and is working towards the designation of Certified Club Manager
            (CCM).  When he is not working, Brendan enjoys spending time with his
            wife, Samantha and daughter, Kennedy. Some of his favorite activities include
            fishing, golfing, cooking, and spending time in nature.
Wendy Thomas, CPA
Director of Finance
Wendy was raised
            right here in Winter Park, where she attended Winter Park High School. Go Wildcats! After graduating in
            2003, she attended the University of Central Florida (UCF), earning an
            undergraduate degree in Business Management and a graduate degree in
            Accounting. She began her accounting career in 2010 at RSM, a public accounting
            firm here in Orlando where she worked in a variety of industries. While working
            there for a period of five years, she developed her passion for private clubs,
            working on them from Hilton Head, SC down to Naples, FL. Wendy has been working
            in the private club sector for the last seven years and is excited for this new
            opportunity at Interlachen. When not working, Wendy spends time with her
            daughter, Mackenzie, and enjoys engaging in different fitness activities and
            going to the beach.
Mikaila Mahoney
Membership & Marketing Director
Mikaila grew up in Naples Florida and studied medical
            assisting while in high school. In July of 2016, she moved to Orlando to study
            Psychology at the University of Central Florida and a couple months later
            started her journey here at Interlachen. In her free time, Mikaila enjoys
            cooking dinner for her friends with her twin sister Michelle. When she is not
            experimenting with new recipes, she enjoys trying out local restaurants, and
            spending time outdoors.
Dennis Bebus
Director of Human Resources
Dennis comes to us from
            Minnesota after relocating to Florida with
            his wife and two daughters in the spring of 2021.  He has extensive human
            resource experience in the non-profit, corporate and military areas. 
            Dennis received both his Bachelor’s Degree in Business Administration, and
            Masters of Art in Human Resource Management from St. Mary’s University of
            Minnesota.  Dennis recently retired
            from the Army National Guard after 23 years of service.
FOOD & BEVERAGE
Natalie Fitzgerald
Catering Director
Natalie began her food & beverage/hospitality career in 1980 where she worked in different levels of management, and gained experience in a multitude of positions. A native of North Royalton, Ohio, her passion of event planning brought her to Florida in 1987 where she continued her career in hotels and resorts. When an opportunity arose to join Interlachen in 1998, she accepted the challenge of working in the private club sector. Natalie is a mother to two sons, Spencer and Devin. In her free time, she enjoys going to the beach, reading, baking and astrology.
Dan Giroux, CEC
Executive Chef
Dan was born and raised in Michigan and began his culinary career at an early age of 15. He has worked in fine dining restaurants, convention centers, and sports venues, until he accepted his first Executive Chef position at a private country club. Dan notes that he has been very fortunate throughout his career to be able to expand his diversity with food through culinary travels and continuing education, as well as having had the opportunity to work with other great chefs from around the globe as the Executive Chef for the North American International Auto Show. When he is not at work, Dan enjoys spending time at home cooking for his wife and four children, he also enjoying fishing, hunting, and playing golf.
GOLF & GREENS
Jay Kennedy
Director of Golf
Jay Kennedy is a PGA Professional and the Director of Golf. He grew up on the coast of North Carolina in Morehead City and graduated from Guliford College. During his time there, he was a two-time All-American in golf and was inducted into the Guliford College Athletic Hall of Fame in 1994. Before he came to Interlachen in 1987, he worked for Harvie Ward at Grand Cypress Resort for five years. He and his wife Valerie have two daughters Hannah and Kathryn
Bryce Gibson, CGCS
Golf Course Superintendent
Bryce was born and raised in Dundee, NY and grew up working on a family Dairy Farm. He attended State University of New York (SUNY) and earned his degree in Plant Science, with a concentration on Golf Course Management. Bryce moved to Florida in 2005 and began his career in Country Clubs. In November 2011, he came to Interlachen as the Assistant Golf Course Superintendent. After 7 years, Bryce was promoted to Golf Course Superintendent in August 2018. When not on the Interlachen golf course, Bryce enjoys golfing and visiting other country clubs around the area. He and his wife Valerie enjoy fishing, boating and spending
            time with family and friends.
TENNIS & AQUATICS
Jeremy Jack
Director of Tennis
Originally from London, Director of Tennis Jeremy Jack grew up surrounded by the game of tennis. He spent his childhood in the UK where his father introduced him to the sport. Jeremy moved to the United States and attended Vincennes University in Indiana and Northeastern State University in Oklahoma where he played college tennis all four years. After teaching professionally for some time, he took a break and enlisted in the United States Army. Jeremy proudly served 5 years and also graduated from the prestigious Army Ranger School.  Jeremy is a certified USPTA Elite Professional as well as a USTA High Performance Coach. Family is an important part of Jeremy’s life. He has three children, two daughters and a son, who live all over the United States. Jeremy loves music, plays guitar on a regular basis and has even played in several bands over the years. He is looking forward to spending more time on the beautiful beaches on both coasts of Florida, as well as the Disney parks.
Justin Allen
Director of Fitness & Aquatics
Justin is a native of Mobile, AL, and has been in aquatics for 12+ years as a Lifeguard, Swim Coach, Swim Instructor, and Aquatics Director. Justin
            started his career with the YMCA of South Alabama as a Lifeguard and Assistant
            Swim Coach in 2008. After a couple of years with the YMCA, Justin accepted the
            Head Swim Coach position at Heron Lakes Country Club. Since 2010, Justin has
            over 10+ years of working in the hospitality industry with stops at the Country
            Club of Mobile, Atlanta Athletic Club, and the Country Club of Birmingham.
            Justin is thrilled to bring his excitement and experience to Interlachen
            Country Club. Justin is also happily married to his beautiful wife, Megan, and
            has two toy poodles, Chip and Dal
e.
FACILITIES
Ron McKelvin
Facilities Director
Ron joined the Interlachen team in June 2018 working in the Golf Department and was promoted to Facilities Manager in September 2018. Ron is retired from the United States Navy, and spent many years teaching High School Navy JROTC. During his teaching career, he served as an Auxilary Florida State Trooper for 13 years. He then served five additional years as a full-time trooper in Volusia and Seminole Counties.

The Club
End Mini-Page 595392
Begin Mini-Page 595393
Our mission is to create value by consistently providing our Members, their families and guests with the highest quality recreation, dining and social experiences in friendly, intimate and exclusive private club setting.
Founded in 1983, the Interlachen name is reflective of the beautiful lakes surrounding it. We're proud to be a certified Audubon Cooperative Sanctuary for our commitment to the enhancement of nature.
Unique to this Club is the challenging Joe Lee designed golf course. In 2007, the course was redesigned by Steve Smyers to build upon Joe Lee's original concept and to further accentuate the raw beauty of the Club's natural surroundings.
Newly renovated in 2015, the resort-style pool, free-standing fitness center, and indoor/outdoor casual dining facility provides a fun and casual atmosphere for the entire family.
At Interlachen, service is both an honor and a pleasure. Our food & beverage team design delightful culinary creations throughout the Club's various dining and lounge environments.
